# Cataloging — Gate C.1 prompt iteration

```elixir
Mix.install([
  {:kino, "~> 0.13"}
])
```

## Why this notebook exists

Gate C.1 (per spec §5 Stream C) is the most important review in the project: cataloging
quality is iterated by hand against a fixture set of source-text inputs, and the
prompt template is edited until the LLM consistently produces high-quality
`%Manillum.Archive.Cataloging.DraftCard{}` outputs.

This notebook is the **Gate C.1 review surface**. It runs the project's `:extract_drafts`
prompt-backed action against the fixtures below, prints a digest of the resulting
`DraftCard`s, and lets the reviewer iterate on the prompt **without** touching the DB,
Oban, or PubSub.

To re-load prompt edits made in `lib/manillum/archive/cataloging/prompt.ex` while the
notebook is connected, run `r Manillum.Archive.Cataloging.Prompt` in the cell below.

## Connecting

This notebook is configured to connect to a running mix project at the worktree root.
In Livebook: **Runtime → Mix standalone** → select this repo's directory. Once
connected, the modules below are available without `Mix.install` — Kino is the only
extra.

